From this week, we start to study the second opening-i2.
In most cases (maybe 95%) black wins in this opening, therefore it is seldom used in serious competitions.
Today we will study the first 4th move.
This is the strongest white move in this opening.
How about the 5th moves? Do you know?
I have a question to you. Is i7 same as i10? Does j7 = h10 ?
Basically, the moves are same, but the distance from the board edge influences the win here.
Sometimes, when 5-i7 brings easy win, the 5-i10 may have some problems because the board edge is closer.
Now, white has many blocks here.
Move 7-7 is very powerful and gives black straight attack in case of any 8th move.
so it's like i 7 up to this point?
